Gaglardi’s Offer for Stars Tops $250 Million, Dallas Morning News Reports

-- B y   N a n c y   K e r c h e v a l
-- 
2011-05-04T04:43:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-04/tom-gaglardi-s-offer-for-dallas-stars-tops-250-million-morning-news-says.html
Canadian businessman Tom Gaglardi
offered more than $250 million for the  National Hockey League ’s
Dallas Stars and a half interest in the American Airlines
Center, the Dallas Morning News reported, citing a person
familiar with negotiations.  Gaglardi, 43, would assume debt and make a cash payment to
lenders, the person told the newspaper. His 30-day exclusive
negotiating window ends in late May, the Morning News said.  The Stars are worth $227 million, according to Forbes.  Gaglardi is president of Northland Properties Corp., which
operates hotels and restaurants in  Canada . He has a net worth of
$2 billion, according to paperwork filed with the NHL, the
Morning News said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Nancy Kercheval in Washington at 
 nkercheval@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Michael Sillup at 
